Operatives of the Lagos Zonal Office of the Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, on Tuesday, arrested 13 persons over alleged involvement in cyber-crime. EFCC in a statement on Tuesday identified the suspects as Idris Ridwan, Shonnaike Adejumobi, Afeez Kareem, Adedire David, Muodozie Patrick, Abidemi Smart, Damilare Gabriel, Foluwako David, Adeleye Smart, Jimoh Olaitan, Olabode Thomas, Akinseye Mayowa and Macaulay Olawale. The commission said they were arrested at their hideout at Gabriel Ajawa Close, Lekki, Lagos State. Their arrest followed credible intelligence on their alleged criminal activities. It added that they will soon be arraigned in Court.